# Server (rhres):

sudo smbpasswd -a $USER
sudo nvim /etc/samba/smb.conf

```
[rhres]
path = /home/$USER/rhres
valid users = $USER
read only = no
browseable = yes
```

sudo systemctl restart smbd

# Client (rhwebsite):

sudo apt update && sudo apt install cifs-utils
mkdir ~/rhwebsite/res
sudo mount -t cifs //server_ip/rhres ~/rhwebsite/res -o username=$USER,password=$SAMBA_PASSWORD,uid=$USER_ID,gid=$GROUP_ID

Auto-mount on boot: Add the mount command (without sudo) to /etc/fstab. Store credentials securely using credentials=/path/to/credentials_file in fstab. Create a file with username=YOUR_USERNAME and password=YOUR_SAMBA_PASSWORD. Restrict permissions with chmod 600.
